      <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════
           CONTENT
      ═══════════════════════════════════ -->
      <div class="s-content">

        <!-- Deck -->
        <section class="s-deck" aria-label="System overview">
          <p class="s-deck-eyebrow">A mechanical reference</p>
          <p class="s-deck-body">The manifesto argues. The system delivers. Every rule on this page is something the production site enforces today — or is about to. If you are shipping, this is your contract.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- ─────────────────────────────────
             01 · FOUNDATIONS
        ───────────────────────────────── -->
        <section id="foundations" class="s-chapter" aria-labelledby="foundations-head">
          <header class="s-chapter-head">
            <span class="s-chapter-num">01</span>
            <h2 id="foundations-head" class="s-chapter-title">Foundations</h2>
            <p class="s-chapter-deck">The non-negotiables. Logo, color, type, grid.</p>
          </header>

          <!-- LOGO -->
          <article class="s-section" id="foundations-logo">
            <header class="s-section-head">
              <span class="s-section-num">1.1</span>
              <h3>Logo — DX monogram</h3>
            </header>
            <p>The monogram is set in False Regular, delivered as outlined SVG — no runtime font dependency. Two letters, no tagline, no lockup. Three approved colorways: dark on light, white on dark, white on accent.</p>
            <div class="s-logo-grid">
              <div class="s-logo-card s-on-light">
                <svg class="s-logo-svg" viewBox="0 0 1484.43 1027.42" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path fill="#050505" d="M134.2,846V169H0L134.2,0h331.66c63.75,0,120.84,9.27,171.28,27.8s93.41,45.94,128.91,82.19,62.73,81.38,81.7,135.36,28.45,116.42,28.45,187.33-9.69,131.12-29.05,183.09c-19.38,51.97-47.02,95.08-82.92,129.33s-79.28,59.62-130.12,76.14-108.12,24.77-171.88,24.77H134.2ZM352.2,677h95.56c26.61,0,52.22-3.62,76.81-10.88s46.38-20.16,65.33-38.7c18.94-18.55,34.06-44.36,45.36-77.42,11.28-33.06,16.94-75.39,16.94-127s-5.45-94.95-16.33-127.61c-10.89-32.66-25.61-58.45-44.16-77.41-18.56-18.94-39.94-31.84-64.12-38.7-24.19-6.84-49.59-10.28-76.2-10.28h-99.19v508Z"/>
                  <path fill="#050505" d="M456.78,0h264.77l200.7,270.72L1127.78,0h257.52l-336.11,441.12,435.25,586.3-336.11-96.72-232.12-313.12-174.09,228.42h-257.52l303.45-400.03L456.78,0Z"/>
                </svg>
                <span class="s-logo-caption">Primary · #050505 on #f4f4f1</span>
              </div>
              <div class="s-logo-card s-on-dark">
                <svg class="s-logo-svg" viewBox="0 0 1484.43 1027.42" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path fill="#f3f0e8" d="M134.2,846V169H0L134.2,0h331.66c63.75,0,120.84,9.27,171.28,27.8s93.41,45.94,128.91,82.19,62.73,81.38,81.7,135.36,28.45,116.42,28.45,187.33-9.69,131.12-29.05,183.09c-19.38,51.97-47.02,95.08-82.92,129.33s-79.28,59.62-130.12,76.14-108.12,24.77-171.88,24.77H134.2ZM352.2,677h95.56c26.61,0,52.22-3.62,76.81-10.88s46.38-20.16,65.33-38.7c18.94-18.55,34.06-44.36,45.36-77.42,11.28-33.06,16.94-75.39,16.94-127s-5.45-94.95-16.33-127.61c-10.89-32.66-25.61-58.45-44.16-77.41-18.56-18.94-39.94-31.84-64.12-38.7-24.19-6.84-49.59-10.28-76.2-10.28h-99.19v508Z"/>
                  <path fill="#f3f0e8" d="M456.78,0h264.77l200.7,270.72L1127.78,0h257.52l-336.11,441.12,435.25,586.3-336.11-96.72-232.12-313.12-174.09,228.42h-257.52l303.45-400.03L456.78,0Z"/>
                </svg>
                <span class="s-logo-caption">Inverse · #f3f0e8 on #060606</span>
              </div>
              <div class="s-logo-card s-on-accent">
                <svg class="s-logo-svg" viewBox="0 0 1484.43 1027.42" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path fill="#fff" d="M134.2,846V169H0L134.2,0h331.66c63.75,0,120.84,9.27,171.28,27.8s93.41,45.94,128.91,82.19,62.73,81.38,81.7,135.36,28.45,116.42,28.45,187.33-9.69,131.12-29.05,183.09c-19.38,51.97-47.02,95.08-82.92,129.33s-79.28,59.62-130.12,76.14-108.12,24.77-171.88,24.77H134.2ZM352.2,677h95.56c26.61,0,52.22-3.62,76.81-10.88s46.38-20.16,65.33-38.7c18.94-18.55,34.06-44.36,45.36-77.42,11.28-33.06,16.94-75.39,16.94-127s-5.45-94.95-16.33-127.61c-10.89-32.66-25.61-58.45-44.16-77.41-18.56-18.94-39.94-31.84-64.12-38.7-24.19-6.84-49.59-10.28-76.2-10.28h-99.19v508Z"/>
                  <path fill="#fff" d="M456.78,0h264.77l200.7,270.72L1127.78,0h257.52l-336.11,441.12,435.25,586.3-336.11-96.72-232.12-313.12-174.09,228.42h-257.52l303.45-400.03L456.78,0Z"/>
                </svg>
                <span class="s-logo-caption">Restricted · #fff on #c00 · logo lockups only</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <ul class="s-rules">
              <li>Minimum clear space: 1× the cap-height of the "D" on all sides.</li>
              <li>Never place on a busy image, gradient, or pattern without a solid backing panel.</li>
              <li>No drop shadows, bevels, strokes, or effects — the letterforms are the design.</li>
              <li>The on-accent colorway is a brand-mark presentation context only. It does not grant permission for red backgrounds in layouts.</li>
              <li>Never lock up with a tagline or wordmark adjacent to the mark.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <!-- COLOR -->
          <article class="s-section" id="foundations-color">
            <header class="s-section-head">
              <span class="s-section-num">1.2</span>
              <h3>Color</h3>
            </header>
            <p>Two authored modes. Light and dark are editorial decisions, not moods — the toggle in the masthead is the real production control, cookie-persisted across every page. Dark mode is a complete variable inversion. No color enters outside this palette. No opacity is created ad hoc.</p>
            <div class="s-swatch-grid">
              <div class="s-swatch" style="--sw: #f4f4f1; --sw-ink: #050505;">
                <div class="s-swatch-chip"></div>
                <div class="s-swatch-meta">
                  <code class="s-swatch-token">--bg</code>
                  <code class="s-swatch-hex">#f4f4f1</code>
                  <span class="s-swatch-role">Paper</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="s-swatch" style="--sw: #050505; --sw-ink: #f4f4f1;">
                <div class="s-swatch-chip"></div>
                <div class="s-swatch-meta">
                  <code class="s-swatch-token">--ink</code>
                  <code class="s-swatch-hex">#050505</code>
                  <span class="s-swatch-role">Ink</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="s-swatch" style="--sw: #c00; --sw-ink: #fff;">
                <div class="s-swatch-chip"></div>
                <div class="s-swatch-meta">
                  <code class="s-swatch-token">--accent</code>
                  <code class="s-swatch-hex">#c00</code>
                  <span class="s-swatch-role">Structural red</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="s-swatch" style="--sw: #060606; --sw-ink: #f3f0e8;">
                <div class="s-swatch-chip"></div>
                <div class="s-swatch-meta">
                  <code class="s-swatch-token">--bg <span class="s-swatch-mode">dark</span></code>
                  <code class="s-swatch-hex">#060606</code>
                  <span class="s-swatch-role">Paper · dark mode</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="s-swatch" style="--sw: #f3f0e8; --sw-ink: #060606;">
                <div class="s-swatch-chip"></div>
                <div class="s-swatch-meta">
                  <code class="s-swatch-token">--ink <span class="s-swatch-mode">dark</span></code>
                  <code class="s-swatch-hex">#f3f0e8</code>
                  <span class="s-swatch-role">Ink · dark mode</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="s-swatch" style="--sw: #ff4d4d; --sw-ink: #060606;">
                <div class="s-swatch-chip"></div>
                <div class="s-swatch-meta">
                  <code class="s-swatch-token">--accent-on-dark</code>
                  <code class="s-swatch-hex">#ff4d4d</code>
                  <span class="s-swatch-role">Small red text on dark</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="s-note"><strong>Accent doctrine.</strong> <code>#c00</code> is identical across both modes for borders, fills, and display text ≥ 18px. For small red text (&lt; 18px) on dark, <code>--accent-on-dark</code> (#ff4d4d, 7.54:1 on #060606) takes over to satisfy WCAG AA.</p>
          </article>

          <!-- TYPOGRAPHY -->
          <article class="s-section" id="foundations-type">
            <header class="s-section-head">
              <span class="s-section-num">1.3</span>
              <h3>Typography</h3>
            </header>
            <p>Two families. One for identity, one for argument. Binary weight — 400 or 700. No 500, no 600. <code>font-synthesis: none</code> site-wide so Anton can't be faux-bolded.</p>
            <div class="s-type-stack">
              <div class="s-type-specimen">
                <div class="s-type-meta">
                  <code>--display</code>
                  <span>Anton · Regular</span>
                  <span class="s-type-role">Identity</span>
                </div>
                <div class="s-type-sample s-sample-display">Refined Brutalism</div>
              </div>
              <div class="s-type-specimen">
                <div class="s-type-meta">
                  <code>--body</code>
                  <span>IBM Plex Sans · 400 / 700</span>
                  <span class="s-type-role">Argument</span>
                </div>
                <div class="s-type-sample s-sample-body">The surfaces behave like pages. The pages behave like arguments. <strong>The arguments behave like sermons you would not interrupt.</strong></div>
              </div>
              <div class="s-type-specimen">
                <div class="s-type-meta">
                  <code>--mono</code>
                  <span>SF Mono / Fira Code</span>
                  <span class="s-type-role">Meta, labels, code</span>
                </div>
                <div class="s-type-sample s-sample-mono">ENTRY № 05 · APR 19, 2026 · FAITH · 18 MIN</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="s-note"><strong>Scale.</strong> 19-step fluid ramp, from <code>--size-1</code> (9.6px meta rail) to <code>--size-19</code> (identity hero name, up to 7.5rem). All sizes live in <code>tokens.css</code>. Component stylesheets pull from the ramp only.</p>
          </article>

          <!-- GRID -->
          <article class="s-section" id="foundations-grid">
            <header class="s-section-head">
              <span class="s-section-num">1.4</span>
              <h3>Grid & spacing</h3>
            </header>
            <p>Strict 4px base. One deliberate slot at 14px (<code>--space-chrome</code>) for button/share-bar rhythm — otherwise every value is a multiple of 4. Consumers call <code>--space-*</code> aliases; raw pixels in component styles are a bug.</p>
            <p class="s-note">Full spacing scale: <code>0 · 4 · 8 · 12 · 14 · 16 · 24 · 32 · 48 · 80</code>. Grid gap defaults to <code>--space-sm</code> (12px). Page-shell padding uses <code>--outer-pad</code>, which adapts at the 760px breakpoint.</p>
          </article>
        </section>

        <!-- ─────────────────────────────────
             02 · VOICE (in progress)
        ───────────────────────────────── -->
        <section id="voice" class="s-chapter s-chapter-stub" aria-labelledby="voice-head">
          <header class="s-chapter-head">
            <span class="s-chapter-num">02</span>
            <h2 id="voice-head" class="s-chapter-title">Voice</h2>
            <p class="s-chapter-deck">How the brand sounds. Editorial tone, microcopy, structural rules.</p>
          </header>
          <div class="s-stub-panel">
            <p class="s-stub-label">Chapter in progress</p>
            <p>Three sections porting from <a class="s-link" href="/brand-legacy/">brand-legacy</a>: Editorial Voice (§06), Microcopy &amp; Interface Voice (§07), Structural Rules (§08). Each will land as its own article with real examples from shipped essays.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- ─────────────────────────────────
             03 · COMPONENTS (in progress)
        ───────────────────────────────── -->
        <section id="components" class="s-chapter s-chapter-stub" aria-labelledby="components-head">
          <header class="s-chapter-head">
            <span class="s-chapter-num">03</span>
            <h2 id="components-head" class="s-chapter-title">Components</h2>
            <p class="s-chapter-deck">Live demos of the production components the essays run on.</p>
          </header>
          <div class="s-stub-panel">
            <p class="s-stub-label">Chapter in progress</p>
            <p>Article components (pull quote, callout, scripture, stat, section head, study note). Homepage components (issue head, identity hero, lane index, plate lead, subscribe manifesto, issue next). Each rendered with its production class — not a clone.</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- ─────────────────────────────────
             04 · SYSTEM (in progress)
        ───────────────────────────────── -->
        <section id="system" class="s-chapter s-chapter-stub" aria-labelledby="system-head">
          <header class="s-chapter-head">
            <span class="s-chapter-num">04</span>
            <h2 id="system-head" class="s-chapter-title">System</h2>
            <p class="s-chapter-deck">The operating contracts. Accessibility, responsive, motion, platform.</p>
          </header>
          <div class="s-stub-panel">
            <p class="s-stub-label">Chapter in progress</p>
            <p>WCAG 2.2 AA baseline. Responsive behavior at 760px. Motion &amp; interaction states (<code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> honored, no bounce easing). Social platform dimensions (four format × two mode matrix).</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Exit -->
        <section class="s-exit" aria-label="Next">
          <p class="s-exit-body">The system is a contract, not a showcase. The actual surfaces it produces live at <a class="s-link" href="/brand/evidence/">brand/evidence</a>.</p>
          <a class="s-link s-exit-back" href="/brand/">← Back to the manifesto</a>
        </section>

      </div>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer-strip" aria-label="Footer">
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="https://instagram.com/ImJustDex" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Instagram</a>
        <span class="footer-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <a href="https://x.com/ImJustDex" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">X</a>
        <span class="footer-sep" aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span>
        <a href="/feed.xml" aria-label="RSS feed">Feed</a>
      </div>
      <span>Built by Dex &middot; Est. 2026</span>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
